				<p>
					Mason Matthews is the co-founder of PolitiPub. The idea came to him one evening while participating in his nightly routine of drinking a beer and scrolling through Facebook. After seeing how divided his friends and family have become in our current era of divided government, he realized that information overload has inadvertently reduced exposure to ideas outside of our own. There is an endless assortment of "news" websites on the internet that provide the dogma that their readership expects rather than the truth they deserve. Through algorithms and corporate sponsorship, our news feeds have evolved into extensions of our egos that seek to validate our views while demonizing the opinions of all who disagree. This is something that he realized must change through the power of hops and the written word. When he's not working to change the world through dialogue, critical thought and empathetic listening, Mason can typically be found enjoying the unparalleled craft beers and open wilderness in his native state of California. He also enjoys reading books- they're a combination of words that formulate ideas which are subsequently printed onto paper and bound between a cover. They're really cool!
				</p>
